Name: squamous cell papilloma
Definition: An extrinsic allergic alveolitis which is caused by inhalation of antigens from avian excreta. The disease has_symptom abrupt onset of dyspnea

Name: breast duct papilloma
Definition: An intraductal papillary breast neoplasm that is has_material_basis_in epithelial tissue on papillae of vascularized connective tissue.

Name: serous surface papilloma
Definition: A carcinosarcoma that has_material_basis_in gland and muscle components.

Name: transitional papilloma
Definition: A sweat gland neoplasm that is composed_of outgrowths of myoepithelial cells from a sweat gland.

Name: gallbladder papillomatosis
Definition: An organ system cancer located_in gastrointestinal tract that is manifested in organs of the gastrointestinal system.

Name: verrucous papilloma
Definition: A fallopian tube benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in the serosa and is characterized by exophytic growth.

Name: skin papilloma
Definition: A fallopian tube benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in the serosa and is characterized by exophytic growth.

Name: inverted papilloma
Definition: A fallopian tube benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in the serosa and is characterized by exophytic growth.

Name: biliary papillomatosis
Definition: A biliary tract benign neoplasm characterized by multiple papillary tumors in the intrahepatic and/or extrahepatic biliary tree.

Name: nasal vestibule papilloma
Definition: A germ cell cancer that presents in childhood.
Synonym: squamous papilloma of the nasal Vestibule

Name: ethmoid sinus inverted papilloma
Definition: An endocrine organ benign neoplasm that is a benign tumor of the glandular type (adenoma) in the adrenal gland.
Synonym: Inverted papilloma of the ethmoid sinus

Name: obsolete metastatic testicular cancer
Definition: An endocrine organ benign neoplasm that is a benign tumor of the glandular type (adenoma) in the adrenal gland.
Synonym: Inverted papilloma of the ethmoid sinus

Name: urinary bladder inverted papilloma
Definition: A benign perivascular tumor that is characterized as a vascular variant of a glomus tumor.

Name: urethra inverted papilloma
Definition: A benign perivascular tumor that is characterized as a vascular variant of a glomus tumor.

Name: maxillary sinus inverted papilloma
Definition: A histiocytic and dendritic cell cancer that is mainly located_in lymph nodes.
Synonym: Inverted papilloma of the maxillary sinus

Name: frontal sinus inverted papilloma
Definition: A cancer of urethra that has recurred after it has been treated. The cancer may come back in the urethra or in other parts of the body.
Synonym: Inverted papilloma of the Frontal sinus

Name: cervix squamous papilloma
Definition: A cervical benign neoplasm that is a polypoid lesion characterized by a single papillary frond with a central fibrovascular core and mature squamous epithelium.
Synonym: squamous papilloma of the Cervix Uteri
